    {
      "id": "ms1-sticky",
      "name": "About this workflow",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [180, 60],
      "parameters": {
        "width": 1400,
        "height": 280,
        "content": "## WF-MS-1 -- Hostfully -> GHL Inbound\n\n**Webhook:** `POST /webhook/hostfully-inbox-message`\n\n**Real webhook payload (4 fields only):** agency_uid, message_uid, event_type, thread_uid.\nFull message data (leadUid, propertyUid, body, type) is fetched from GET /api/v3.2/messages/{message_uid}.\n\n**Flow:** Webhook -> Config -> ACK 200 -> Agency check -> event_type filter -> Build Dedup Key -> MessageDedup lookup -> if new: Fetch Full Message -> Unwrap -> direction filter (GUEST_TO_HOST only) -> ThreadContactMap lookup -> if cached use it, else fetch lead + WF-MS-3 -> POST GHL inbound (type=Email) -> write dedup + map.\n\n**No Custom Conversation Provider needed.** Messages are posted as type Email. GHL outbound replies are received via standard GHL webhook (Settings -> Integrations -> Webhooks -> OutboundMessage event -> WF-MS-2 URL).\n\n**Config node:** update AGENCY_UID_WEBHOOK, AGENCY_UID_API before activating.\n**GHL credential:** replace VwJj55d4veBRjPmF on Post Inbound Message to GHL node."
      }
    }
